    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1974-01-30T22:11:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1974-01-30T22:11:00-05:00" n="326"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d326">
                <head>326. Telegram 020401 From the Department of State to the Embassy in the
                    Philippines, January 31, 1974, 0311Z.<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d326fn1"
                        >Source: National Archives, <persName corresp="#p_nixon-richard-m"
                            >Nixon</persName> Presidential Materials, <gloss target="#t_nsc"
                            >NSC</gloss> Files, Box 558, Country Files, Far East, Philippines, 1
                        January 1974. Secret; Cherokee; Priority; <gloss target="#t_nodis"
                            >Nodis</gloss>; Eyes Only Ambassador. Drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_hummel-arthur-w-jr">Hummel</persName>; cleared by <persName
                            corresp="#p_lord-winston">Lord</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_scowcroft-brent">Scowcroft</persName>; and approved by
                            <persName corresp="#p_kissinger-henry-a">Kissinger</persName>.</note>
                    <note n="2" type="summary" xml:id="d326fn2">The Department conveyed the U.S.
                        position regarding the Spratly Islands.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1974-01-31T03:11:00+00:00">January 31, 1974, 0311Z</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>TELEGRAM<lb/>Department of State<lb/>020401</p>
                <p>P 310311Z JAN 74 ZFF4</p>
                <p>FM <gloss target="#t_secstate">SECSTATE</gloss> WASHDC<lb/>TO AMEMBASSY MANILA
                    PRIORITY 4324</p>
                <p>E.O. 11652: GDS<lb/>TAGS: PBOR, MARR, MOPS, <gloss target="#t_rp">RP</gloss>,
                    CH</p>
                <p>SUBJECT: POSITION WITH RESPECT TO SPRATLEY ISLANDS<lb/>EYES ONLY AMBASSADOR</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>YOUR TEL 0998 <gloss target="#t_para">PARA</gloss> 5 RAISES FOUR ISSUES: <list>
                            <label>(A)</label>
                            <item>LEGAL POSITION ON US OBLIGATION TO ACT IF PHL FORCES ARE ATTACKED
                                IN SPRATLEYS; WE HAVE SENT STATE 017663 WHICH IS PARTIAL AND
                                PRELIMINARY RESPONSE AND WE ARE STILL LOOKING INTO US
                                POSITION.</item>
                            <label>(B)</label>
                            <item>ASSURANCE TO YOU THAT US IS CONDUCTING SURVEILLANCE TO GUARD
                                AGAINST SURPRISE ATTACK ON SPRATLEYS; THE HIGHEST APPROPRIATE LEVEL
                                HERE HAS DECIDED THAT SUCH SURVEILLANCE WILL NOT <gloss
                                    target="#t_rpt">RPT</gloss> NOT BE UNDERTAKEN.</item>
                            <label>(C)</label>
                            <item>YOU SUGGEST “DEMARCHE TO PEKING TO WARN CHINESE THAT MILITARY
                                ACTION AGAINST PHL FORCES WOULD ENGAGE US OBLIGATIONS”; A NUMBER OF
                                FACTORS RULE THIS OUT AT THIS TIME: THE LACK OF TIME: THE
                                UNCERTAINTY OF US POSITION (A, ABOVE), LACK OF ANY INDICATIONS THAT
                                    <gloss target="#t_prc">PRC</gloss> INTENDS TO MOVE AGAINST
                                SPRATLEYS, AND OTHERS.</item>
                            <label>(D)</label>
                            <item>YOUR REQUEST FOR AUTHORITY TO CONSULT WITH PHL OFFICIALS SHOULD,
                                OBVIOUSLY, AWAIT FURTHER EXAMINATION OF POINT (A).</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>WE WILL BE REPLYING IN LESS RESTRICTED CHANNEL ON POINTS OTHER THAN B AND
                        C.</item>
                </list>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_kissinger-henry-a">KISSINGER</persName>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
